		<title>Creative Writing Prompts: 30 Exercises for Creativity Muscles</title>
		<link>http://blog.a-pluss.com/2012/02/28/creative-writing-prompts-30-exercises-for-creativity-muscles/</link>
		<comments>http://blog.a-pluss.com/2012/02/28/creative-writing-prompts-30-exercises-for-creativity-muscles/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 28 Feb 2012 13:14:48 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>Sandra Jackson</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[General Writing Help]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.a-pluss.com/?p=1942</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Do you know that creativity is like a muscle? The more you exercise it, the stronger it becomes. No matter if it is your own decision to find prompts for creative writing or your tutors have encouraged you, here you will find unique topics you can sink your teeth into. &#160; These 30 effective creative [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="http://blog.a-pluss.com/wp-content/uploads/a-pluss.com/2012/02/creative-writing-prompts.jpg" alt="creative-writing-prompts" title="creative-writing-prompts" width="200" height="150" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1952" />Do you know that creativity is like a muscle? The more you exercise it, the stronger it becomes. No matter if it is your own decision to find prompts for creative writing or your tutors have encouraged you, here you will find unique topics you can sink your teeth into.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
These 30 effective creative writing activities will become a splendid exercise program for your creativity.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
<strong>Creative writing prompts: story starters</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>One day you buy a bottle of coke, open it and see a jinn sitting in the bottle. You are granted three wishes, but these wishes cannot be selfish…</li>
<li>One sunny morning you wake up, go to the bathroom, look into the mirror and… You see your old enemy (best friend/ Eminem/Angelina Jolie) in the mirror. You scream and understand that you have exchanged your bodies and minds…</li>
<li>Moving to a new house, you find a letter written by the previous owners. You are at a loss because the letter says…</li>
<li>Somebody rings your door and runs away quickly. When you open the door, there is nobody, but you discover a basket…</li>
<li>One day your best friend asks you to fetch a ball from his/her room. Searching the ball, you find night vision glasses and other spy equipment…</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Creative writing prompts: story titles</strong></p>
<ol start=6>
<li>A man who always tells the truth.</li>
<li>Be careful what you wish for, you just might get it.</li>
<li>Why not learn from the mistakes of others?</li>
<li>If cell phones did not exist, they would have been invented.</li>
<li>The most unconventional and breathtaking chess game of my life.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Creative writing prompts: three elements</strong><br />
&nbsp;<br />
Try to combine these three elements in one story:</p>
<ol start=11>
<li>a school bus, global warming, an awkward situation;</li>
<li>Halloween, racist remark, lost keys;</li>
<li>green shoes, a white lie, scream;</li>
<li>vanilla ice-cream, sweet revenge, high temperature;</li>
<li>rainforest, digital camera, mild reproach.</li>
</ol>
<p><span id="more-1942"></span><br />
<img src="http://blog.a-pluss.com/wp-content/uploads/a-pluss.com/2012/02/creative-writing-prompt.jpg" alt="creative-writing-prompt" title="creative-writing-prompt" width="200" height="224" class="alignleft size-full wp-image-1958" /><strong>Creative writing prompts: final phrases</strong><br />
&nbsp;<br />
Make these sentences the final phrases of your stories:</p>
<ol start=16>
<li>It was the most remarkable lesson I ever learned from my cat.</li>
<li>Since then, I never got online anymore.</li>
<li>Nevertheless, hope never dies.</li>
<li>Losing the tickets was a blessing in disguise.</li>
<li>I never thought that mere chance could change my life.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Creative writing prompts: lists</strong></p>
<ol start=21>
<li>Create a list of ten things one can do to lose a guy (girl) in ten days.</li>
<li>Ten most common gifts (such as scented candles or picture frames).</li>
<li>Ten ‘white lies’ your parents or friends ever told you to comfort you.</li>
<li>Ten things you could do to entertain yourself if there was no electricity.</li>
<li>Ten questions to well-known characters (historical, modern or fictional).</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Creative writing prompts: what if</strong></p>
<ol start=26>
<li>What if people could buy happiness?</li>
<li>What if people had no feelings and emotions?</li>
<li>What if all people could read the thoughts of others?</li>
<li>What if humans could live forever?</li>
<li>What if Santa Claus existed and you did not receive presents in the recent years only because you were not good enough?</li>
</ol>
<p>As you see, these creative writing topics are just perfect for stretching and strengthening your creativity muscles. Choose any creative writing prompt from this list and enjoy bursts of creativity and excellent grades for your creative papers.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
